tspan.tspan: Sequel is a CV & Trigger sequencer, inspired by hardware analogue sequencer
Each step of each of Sequel's 3 rows has a CV Knob
, and an active step led. The voltage outputted by each row's CV
is equal to the value of the CV knob
is controlled by switching on or off the gate button
There are two methods for controlling the speed of Sequel. You can use the
internal clock controlled by the speed knob
, or you can feed an external clock
source into Sequel via the external clock in port
One of the most powerful features of Sequel is it's per-row clock
Set a clock divide value for each row using the clock divide
, the value is indicated via the clock divide displays
The clock divide value determines how many clock inputs are
needed before that row will progress to a new step. This means
that Sequel's rows are able to become out of sync with
eachother, allowing for the creation of interesting polyrhythms.
Sequel is capable of two different gate modes. The active gate
